President Barack Obama has signed an Executive Order to create a Presidential Emergency Board to help resolve a dispute between the Long Island Rail Road Company and its employees. The board will hear evidence and deliver a report to the President within 30 days, recommending how the dispute should be resolved. President Obama has appointed Ira F. Jaffe as the Chair of the board, along with Roberta Golick and Arnold M. Zack as members. Jaffe has extensive experience as an arbitrator and mediator of labor and employment disputes, Golick has been an arbitrator and mediator since 1974, and Zack has been an arbitrator and mediator of over 5,000 labor disputes since 1957.